% Frontend Development Standards
% React Component Guidelines for InvoiceIQ

1. React 18+, TypeScript, functional components with hooks
2. Use camelCase for variables and functions, PascalCase for components
3. Use Tailwind CSS for styling; prefer utility classes
4. Component props must be typed (TypeScript interfaces)
5. All components must have prop defaults and proper error boundaries
6. Use React Query or SWR for data fetching
7. Implement proper loading states with skeleton loaders
8. Use react-dropzone for file uploads, react-table for data tables
9. Accessibility: proper aria-labels, keyboard navigation, contrast ratios
10. All components must have unit tests with React Testing Library
